A 35-year-old driver, Monsuru Lukuman, has been remanded by an Osogbo Magistratesâ€™ Court for reckless driving and parking at an unauthorized place. Police prosecutor, Inspector Jacob Akintunde told the court that the accused person committed the offence on September 29, 2020 around 4:45 pm at Dada Estate area, in Osogbo. According to the prosecutor, Akintunde alleged that the accused drove one Coaster Bus with registration number YA 635 EPE in a dangerous manner. He further disclosed that the driver drove on the public highway without road worthiness and also caused obstruction by parking at unauthorized place. The offence committed is contrary to and punishable under Sections 146,18 Cap 146 Vol ll Law of Osun State 2002 and Section 155 Amendment of RTA of Nigeria 2015. The accused person pleaded not guilty to the allegation preferred against him. Defence Counsel, S.O Ola prayed the court to grant his client bail in most liberal term. In his ruling, Magistrate Modupe Awodele ordered that the accused should be remanded at Ilesa Correctional Centre. The Magistrate further adjourned the case till October 8, 2020.